news.title: Pay property tax by June 30 and get 10% rebate: Nagpur civic body
news.para: The civic body has also announced 10% and 5% rebate on property tax for those paying up before June 30 and December 31, respectively.

news.title: Dubai's Emaar Properties reports $610 million profit in Q1 2022
news.para: Emaar said it had a sales backlog of $12.3 billion at the end of the first quarter, which will be recognised in the future.

news.title: Flat owners in Maradu not entitled to any interest on amounts paid by them to builders: SC
news.para: ​A bench of Justices L Nageswara Rao and B R Gavai said in the present case, the flat-owners have purchased their apartments by paying installments somewhere between 2007 and 2013 depending on the construction of the particular building complex.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance aims Rs 7,200 crore home loans with ADB in Telangana, Andhra by 2025
news.para: The company said with a total disbursement of Rs 2,448 crore in these two states, it benefitted over 17,000 households as on March 31, 2022.

news.title: Citizens fume over delay in MahaRERA orders' execution
news.para: While the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) bench issues the orders within its time-frame, citizens have complained of waiting from five months to even two years for the orders to get implemented.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government seeks housing scam report from GDA
news.para: ​The move comes days after the state government suspended former Ghaziabad district magistrate Nidhi Kesarwani in connection with alleged irregularities in acquiring land for the DME.

news.title: Gurugram: Buyers protest, seek action plan on completion of Mahira Homes
news.para: More than 1,500 homebuyers, most of whom have already paid 100% of the amount to the developer, have been left in the lurch, with the DTCP recently cancelling the licence of the project and recommending the registration of an FIR against Mahira Infratech Pvt Ltd (formerly, Sai Asina Farms Pvt Ltd) for “forging documents and fabricating bank guarantees”.

news.title: Online auction of 500 residential plots in Noida next month
news.para: The plots will be allotted through e-auction, following norms similar to those of the Delhi Development Authority. It will be the first time that plots will be allocated through e-auction in Noida.

news.title: Housing ministry to assess extent of dilutions in rules by states of central RERA
news.para: This comes after the Central Advisory Council (CAC) headed by Union housing minister Hardeep Singh Puri recommended to the ministry to ensure that no entity dilutes the rules under RERA.

news.title: SC directs Rajasthan government to take stringent measures to stop illegal mining of bajri
news.para: The top court also directed the state government to grant mining leases in favour of 68 lessees who have obtained environmental clearance without further delay.

news.title: HCC's net profit drops 80% to Rs 30.88 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income during the quarter under review stood at Rs 2,946.16 crore, compared to Rs 2,398.38 crore in the year-ago period. Total expenses increased to Rs 2,884.36 crore from Rs 2,618.48 crore earlier.

news.title: Nashik civic body serves fresh reminders to 25 builders
news.para: NMC had sent notices to builders involved in 65 projects that came up over 4,000 sq metre of land. Only 35 builders have furnished information related to the project.

news.title: Nisus Finance makes exit from Advaitha Ventures' housing project in Bengaluru
news.para: The deal is among few such instances as many large non-banking finance companies (NBFCs) and banks are finding it difficult to get a complete exit from their legacy investments in the real estate sector post Covid19 pandemic.

news.title: Kolkata: ED raids Abhijata Constructions, promoters in money laundering case
news.para: The money laundering case against the company and its promoters stems from several Kolkata Police FIRs where numerous home buyers alleged "non delivery of homes by the company in spite of getting full payments from the buyers," the ED said in a statement.

news.title: Owner-tenant dispute on deposit can go to arbritrator: HC
news.para: HC held arbitration can be invoked as the dispute was over a claim of damages in a security deposit refund and not rent money or any other monthly charge.
